== Geography ==

=== Climate ===

As with the rest of the [[British Isles]] and the Midlands, Coventry experiences a [[maritime climate]] with cool summers and mild winters. The nearest Met Office weather station is Coundon/Coventry Bablake. Temperature extremes recorded in Coventry range from {{convert|-18.2|C|F}} in February 1947, to {{convert|35.2|C|F}} in July 2019.&lt;ref&gt;{{cite web| publisher = Bablake Weather| url = http://www.bablakeweather.co.uk/2019-extremes| title = 2019 extremes in Coventry| accessdate = 27 July 2019| archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20190411124155/http://www.bablakeweather.co.uk/2019-extremes| archive-date = 11 April 2019| url-status = dead}}&lt;/ref&gt;  The lowest temperature reading of recent years was {{convert|-10.8|C|F}} during December 2010.&lt;ref&gt;{{cite web| publisher = [[Met Office]]| url = http://metofficenews.wordpress.com/2010/12/20/| title = 2010 temperature| access-date = 12 November 2011| archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20120320225501/http://metofficenews.wordpress.com/2010/12/20/| archive-date = 20 March 2012| url-status = dead}}&lt;/ref&gt;&lt;ref&gt;{{cite web | publisher = Bablake Weather | url = http://bws.users.netlink.co.uk/last%20years%20stats.htm | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20070728111339/http://bws.users.netlink.co.uk/last%20years%20stats.htm | url-status = dead | archivedate = 28 July 2007 | title = 2010 temperature }}&lt;/ref&gt;

{{Coventry weatherbox}}

===City boundaries===

Coventry forms the largest part of the [[Coventry and Bedworth Urban Area]]. The city proper covers an area of almost 100&amp;nbsp;km square.

The protected [[West Midlands Green Belt]], which surrounds the city on all sides, has prevented the expansion of the city into both the administrative county of [[Warwickshire]] and the metropolitan borough of [[Solihull]] (the [[Meriden Gap]]), and has helped to prevent the coalescence of the city with surrounding towns such as [[Kenilworth]], [[Nuneaton]], [[Leamington Spa]], [[Warwick]], [[Rugby, Warwickshire|Rugby]] and [[Balsall Common]].

