Coventry has an ethnic minority population which represented 33.4% of the population at the 2011 census.&lt;ref name=&quot;ons.gov.uk&quot;&gt;{{Cite web |url=http://www.ons.gov.uk/ons/rel/census/2011-census/key-statistics-for-local-authorities-in-england-and-wales/rft-table-ks201ew.xls |title=Archived copy |access-date=25 December 2012 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160224143452/http://www.ons.gov.uk/ons/rel/census/2011-census/key-statistics-for-local-authorities-in-england-and-wales/rft-table-ks201ew.xls |archive-date=24 February 2016 |url-status=live }}&lt;/ref&gt; The ethnic minority population is concentrated in the [[Foleshill]] and the [[St. Michael's, Coventry|St. Michael's]] wards.&lt;ref name=&quot;2011census&quot;/&gt; [[Islam]] is the largest non-Christian religion, but the composition of the ethnic minority population is not typical of the UK with significant numbers of other [[South Asian]]s. Both [[Sikh]] and [[Hindu]] religions are represented significantly higher than in the rest of the West Midlands in general.&lt;ref&gt;{{cite web|url=http://www.neighbourhood.statistics.gov.uk/dissemination/LeadTableView.do?a=7&amp;b=6275069&amp;c=coventry&amp;d=13&amp;e=61&amp;g=6364318&amp;i=1001x1003x1032x1004&amp;m=0&amp;r=1&amp;s=1364680630599&amp;enc=1&amp;dsFamilyId=2579|title=Area: Coventry (Local Authority) â€“ Religion, 2011 (QS208EW)|work=Neighbourhood Statistics|publisher=Office for National Statistics|accessdate=17 July 2013|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130522052232/http://www.neighbourhood.statistics.gov.uk/dissemination/LeadTableView.do?a=7&amp;b=6275069&amp;c=coventry&amp;d=13&amp;e=61&amp;g=6364318&amp;i=1001x1003x1032x1004&amp;m=0&amp;r=1&amp;s=1364680630599&amp;enc=1&amp;dsFamilyId=2579|archive-date=22 May 2013|url-status=live}}&lt;/ref&gt;
* 66.6% identify as [[White British]], compared to 79.2% in the West Midlands Region and 79.8% in England.&lt;ref name=&quot;ons.gov.uk&quot;/&gt; 
* 33.4% identify as non-White British, compared to 20.8% in the West Midlands Region and 20.2% in England.

The non-White British population identifies as follows:
* 7.2% as Other White ([[Irish Briton|White Irish]], [[Irish Traveller]] and [[White Other]], including mostly other Europeans), compared to 3.6% in the West Midlands Region and 5.7% in England.
* 2.7% identify as Mixed/Multiple-ethnic group, compared to 2.4% in the West Midlands Region and 2.2% in England.
* 16.3% identify as Asian/Asian British (including [[British Indian|Indian]], [[British Pakistani|Pakistani]], [[British Bangladeshi|Bangladeshi]], [[British Chinese|Chinese]] and [[British Asian|other South Asian groups]]), compared to 10.8% in the West Midlands Region and 7.7% in England;.
* 5.5% identify as Black/Black British (including [[Black British|Black African]], [[Black British|Black Caribbean]] and other black), compared to 3.2% in the West Midlands Region and 3.4% in England.
* 1.6% identify as Other (including [[Arab]] and [[Other ethnic group (United Kingdom Census)|others]]), compared to 0.9% in the West Midlands Region and 1.0% in England.
